parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Seat Occupant Detection Mat Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seat occupant detection mat can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the deactivation of the front passenger airbag, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: the "Passenger Airbag Off" light comes on
and the airbag may not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: the airbag may not deploy in a crash
and the horn may not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the deactivation of the airbag, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: the steering wheel buttons do not work
and the paddle shifter does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of power while driving, loss of headlights, and failure of airbags, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Complete loss of electrical power while driving
and loss of power to doors and windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause doors to become stuck, trapping passengers inside, which can be a safety hazard in case of an emergency.
symptoms: Doors will not unlock with key fob or internal button
doors will not open from inside or outside

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight wiring can cause headlights to short and fail, leading to reduced visibility while driving at night, which can increase the risk of accidents.
The failure of the heated seat can cause burns to the driver or passenger, and in some cases, can lead to a fire.
symptoms: and smoke appearing from the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor wiring can cause the blower motor to overheat, leading to a fire hazard.
symptoms: Burning smell coming from the blower
and hot air blowing from the vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Heated Seat Malfunction and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the heated seat can cause burns, fires, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The heated seat becomes excessively hot
and a burning smell. In some cases
the seat heater can catch fire
or burn holes in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical failure of the heated seat can cause a short circuit, leading to a fire hazard, burns, or electrical shock.
